<TITLE> Alleged extremist killed by bomb </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Pabna, Apr 21 (bdnews24.com)  An alleged extremist was killed in a bomb attack by rivals in Pabna on Wednesday, police said. The dead, Selim Hossain, 32, is the son of Mohammad Alam of Madhupur village. Police said that Selim was a regional leader of ML Janojuddha, a banned extremist outfit. Jamil Ahmed, police superintendent of Pabna, said that the attack might have been over establishing supremacy. Atgharia police chief Enamul Karim told bdnews24.com that Selim was in a secret meeting with his associates at around 6am at Shibpur village of Atgharia upazila. Their rivals threw a bomb on them at that time and Selim was killed on the spot, he added. Selim has several cases, including murder, against him in different police stations in Pabna. bdnews24.c
